The paper deals with the complexity of verifying finite concurrent systems through Linearizability, which involves both logic and data structures. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also involves programming languages (cs.PL), distributed computing (cs.DC), and formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL), which are all relevant to the topic.
